# Personal Website — frontend + BFF

Next.js chat UI and BFF. Scheduling, LLM, and voice STT/TTS belong in a **separate agent API service** — do not add them here.

## Before you edit

| If you are… | Read first |
|-------------|------------|
| Any non-trivial change | `docs/project_structure.md` |
| UI/BFF flows, session, voice+text merge | `docs/architecture.md` |
| Security rollout / Turnstile / rate limits / session cookie | `docs/security.md` |
| Route Handlers or `agent-client.ts` | `docs/agent_api_contract.md` + rule `next-api-routes` |
| LiveKit / voice UI | rule `livekit-voice` |
| Chat components / Zustand store | rule `chat-ui` |
| Agent graph, worker, telephony, calendar | optional: agent API repo `docs/` if present in workspace (see `.cursorrules`) |

After architectural changes, update the relevant `docs/` file in the same session.

## Stack

Next.js 16 · React 19 · TypeScript · Tailwind · shadcn/ui · Vercel AI SDK · LiveKit React SDK · Zustand

## Layering (mandatory)

`Browser UI` → `Route Handlers (BFF)` → compatible agent API (HTTP + LiveKit worker)

Never put LLM, calendar, or Deepgram logic in UI or Route Handlers. See `docs/project_structure.md`.

## Conventions

- Minimal diffs; match existing style; no drive-by refactors
- Dependencies: `npm install` / `npm run dev`
- Do not commit unless explicitly asked
- Do not add tests or markdown files unless requested — **except** `docs/tmp/**` when user enabled it (names `docs/tmp`); see rule `docs-tmp`
- **`docs/tmp/`:** default **skip**. Use only if user names `docs/tmp` in chat, or `docs/tmp/.active` exists and the task continues that feature — then read rule `docs-tmp`
- Entry page: `src/app/page.tsx` → `ChatPanel`
